subSubSection.paragraph:
Glaessner (1928)
reported the species from the Helvetian (Early Miocene) of Jahring (today's Jarenina, 
Slovenia
) in the Styrian Basin. He, however, did not provide figures. The re-examination of the material by the senior author confirms the identification of the material (
Figs 8A–B
).
